caption.p: Concentration-dependent increases in intracellular Reactive Oxygen Species (ROS) elicited by Compound 1 in HeLa cells, presented as fold increases compared to the negative control, following 3 h exposure of HeLa cells to Compound 1. Each bar represents Mean ± SEM (n=3); αp<0.01 versus control using one-way ANOVA followed by Dunnett’s post hoc multiple-comparisons test.
